  "notes": "Vietnamese in Chữ Quốc ngữ (Latin script). 6-tone language: ngang (◌̄/unmarked), huyền (◌̀), sắc (◌́), hỏi (◌̉), ngã (◌̃), nặng (◌̣). Northern (Hanoi) dialect mappings given; Southern dialect differs (D→j, R→j, S→s, X→s). Two implosive stops: B=/ɓ/, Đ=/ɗ/. Final consonants: -c/-ch/-p/-t are unreleased. Vowel Ă = short /a/, Â = central /ə/, Ơ = /əː/, Ư = /ɯ/.",
